name: Lenwebbia prominens N.Snow & Guymer
occurrenceRemarks: Locally frequent small tree 4 m x 4 m. Fruits black. Seeds collected from > 30 plants.
habitat: Gully with regenerating rainforest post clearance. Dominated by Cinnamomum camphora, also with Tristaniopsis laurina, understorey with Ligustrum sinense, Lenwebbia prominens, Blechnum sp. etc. Rocky soil, with rhyolite boulders.
locality: 7.8 km along Byrill Creek Road from Kyogle to Murwillumbah Road, at causeway crossing of Byrill Ctreek.

name: Lenwebbia prominens N.Snow & Guymer
occurrenceRemarks: Locally uncommon small tree 5 m x 6 m. Two plants seen, only one with seeds, seeds colelcted from this tree only. Fruits dull black at maturity.
habitat: Gentle south facing slope near top of ridge. Rainforest with Ceratopetalum apetalum, Endiandra introrsa, Tristaniopsis collina, Acacia orites, Callicoma serratifolia, Acrotriche aggregata, Uromyrtus australis, Lomandra spicata. Shallow pale rocky soil, on rhyolite.
locality: Gibbergunyah Road, at the start of the Nightcap Track, Nightcap National Park.
